      "preview_head": "Annual (Vol. 4) - Batman: The Dark Knight Returns to Gotham! : Although this was published in the mid-'80s during a different era within DC Comics' continuity timeline adjustments known as Crisis on I",
      "preview_tail": "troduced Wonder Woman's sister Hades as a villainess in her own right. These are just some examples of what was happening with DC characters during that year, but remember this is based on publication",
      "full_text": "Annual (Vol. 4) - Batman: The Dark Knight Returns to Gotham! : Although this was published in the mid-'80s during a different era within DC Comics' continuity timeline adjustments known as Crisis on Infinite Earth, it's worth noting that some stories from earlier years were reprinted or referenced. - Wonder Woman #217: This issue introduced Wonder Girl (Cassandra Sandsmark), who would become an important character in the future of both her own series and other DC titles. However, focusing specifically to 1972: - The introduction/reintroduction/continuation/expansion upon various characters such as Black Lightning by writer Dwayne McDuffie began during this period. His work on Green Lantern/Green Arrow #63 in December of that year was pivotal. Please note: Some events may have been published later but set earlier, or vice versa due to the nature and history rewriting practices within comic book storytelling. - Detective Comics (Vol 1) No.428: This issue introduced Wonder Woman's sister Hades as a villainess in her own right. These are just some examples of what was happening with DC characters during that year, but remember this is based on publication",
      "avg_prediction": 0.1909,
